"""Qt 5.14.2 toolchain MCP server (local stdio).

Wraps qmake / mingw32-make / windeployqt so Claude can scaffold, build, run,
deploy and clean Qt Widgets GUI projects without leaving the conversation.

Environment overrides (set before launching the MCP server):
  QT_MCP_QT_ROOT      - 64-bit Qt install dir (default E:\\Download_tools\\QT\\5.14.2\\mingw73_64)
  QT_MCP_QT_32_ROOT   - 32-bit Qt install dir
  QT_MCP_MINGW_BIN    - MinGW bin dir (g++.exe + mingw32-make.exe live here)
  QT_MCP_QTCREATOR    - qtcreator.exe path (qt_creator_open / qt_creator_run)
  QT_MCP_SANDBOX      - sandbox root for all inputs/outputs
  QT_MCP_JSON         - "1" to append a `--- json --- {ok,data|error}` trailer to every tool
  QT_MCP_QT_VERSION   - Qt version string, used in error messages only
"""

